STORY COUNTY WIND, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Story County Wind, LLC ("Story County") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Story County generating facility ("Story County Facility").
Story County is a wind turbine generating facility located in Story County, Iowa. The Story County Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by ITC Midwest, LLC and under the operational control of the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Story County's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Story County Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Story County's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Story County shall be subject to Schedule 2 of MISO's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT: The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $670,000.00. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $55,833.33.
